{"id":"project-LICHEN-seo0","title":"hybrid.rs: pending queue eviction doesn't consider priority","description":"File: rust/lichen-node/src/hybrid.rs:309-316

When the pending packet queue for a destination is full, queue_pending evicts the oldest packet regardless of priority:

```rust
pub fn queue_pending(&mut self, data: Vec<u8>, dst: [u8; 16], now_ms: u32) {
    let pending = PendingPacket {
        data,
        destination: dst,
        queued_at_ms: now_ms,
    };
    let queue = self.pending_queue.entry(dst).or_default();
    if queue.len() >= self.max_pending_per_dest {
        queue.pop_front(); // Drop oldest - ignores priority
    }
    queue.push_back(pending);
    // ...
}
```

Impact: A high-priority packet waiting for route discovery could be evicted in favor of a low-priority packet that arrives later.

Note: PendingPacket doesn't have a priority field, so this would require adding priority support to the pending queue.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:36:24.01969Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:36:24.019755Z"}
